Chantal Rouleau was one of Montreal’s first deputies to hit an alarm.
As mayor of the district of Rivière-des-Prairies, in the eastern part of the island, she opposed the sale of a municipal estate from 2010, which was acquired for $5 million and resold for 1.6 million to builders in the booming real estate market.
70% black money in election campaigns
