We are about to clean up the wound, but we would need an investigative unit dedicated only to Montreal, as well as supervision to prevent a return to questionable practices.
How to clean.
Regularly.
Jacques Duchesneau, for his part, notes that "officials have stolen several hundred million dollars", but is especially concerned about the role of "mandators who are in the picture about the tactics" if they were not involved in the fraud!
Based on a 70% share of black money in the funding of Quebec’s election campaigns, he jokes: “I was told that this was just a weak scratch of reality.”
The Quebec government proposes to limit donations to parties to $100, which it says would not change the situation: “As long as campaign spending is not strictly limited, black money will be in circulation in politics.”
He recommends a complete revision of the system for the procurement of public procurement and the financing of the parties: "We cannot fall deeper; by going to the bottom of things with courage, we can rebuild the house on a more solid basis with more controls and laws."
If this history damages the international reputation of Quebec and that of Montreal, Mr. Duchesneau urges those who laugh about taking a look at their own backyard...
